'''Sumidagawa Shrine''' (隅田川神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[Sumida Ward]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]]. The surrounding area is part of {{ill|Higashi-Shirahige Park|ja|東白鬚公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashi-Shirahige Park|qq=}}.

== Enshrined Deities ==
The shrine venerates the following deities:
* {{ill|Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|lt=Hayaakitsuhiko-no-Kami|ja|速秋津日子神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ハヤアキツヒコ・ハヤアキツヒメ}}
* {{ill|Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|lt=Hayaakitsuhime-no-Kami|ja|速秋津比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ハヤアキツヒコ・ハヤアキツヒメ}}
* {{ill|Ame-no-torifune|lt=Torinoiwakusufune-no-Kami|ja|鳥之石楠船神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-torifune|qq=}}
* {{ill|Ōkajikidohime-no-Kami|ja|大楫木戸姫神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkajikidohime-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}

== History ==
The founding of this shrine is unknown, but legend attributes its establishment to [[:en:Minamoto no Yoritomo|Minamoto no Yoritomo]]. Originally named '''Ukishima Shrine''', it was historically referred to by various names such as Suijin Shrine, Suijin-gū, and Ukishima-gū, and has been affectionately called "Suijin-sama." In 1872, it was renamed to its current title.

In addition to serving as the local [[:en:Chinjugami|Chinjugami]], the shrine is considered the guardian deity of the Sumida River area. It has attracted devotion from water transportation workers, boatmen, and people working in the water trade due to its association with "water gods."

== Stone Monuments ==
The shrine grounds feature a signpost written by Edo-period [[:en:Gesaku|Gesaku]] writer {{ill|Santō Kyōzan|ja|山東京山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Santō Kyōzan|qq=}} and a poetry monument dedicated to {{ill|Kadosu Manako|ja|鹿都部真顔|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kadosu Manako|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 鹿津部真顔}}, a master of [[:en:Kyōka|Kyōka]].

== Access ==
* A 10-minute walk from [[:en:Kanegafuchi Station|Kanegafuchi Station]] ({{OSM map route|start=35.73337,139.81991|goal=35.73274,139.81277|name=Route Directions}}).
